Great news for the Salem-Keizer area! The Department of Transportation announced awarded a grant of over $1,000,000 to replace outdated buses. Investments in transit such as this help hardworking Oregonians get to work and allow our cities to flourish. https://schrader.house.gov/newsroom/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=392626 …

🦈🌊I just voted to ban the trade of shark fins in the U.S. The inhumane practice of shark finning entails cutting off a shark’s fins, while the animal is still alive, and discarding the body. Some shark populations have declined by as much as 90% because of this. 🦈🌊

I spoke on the House floor this morning in honor of #NativeAmericanHeritageMonth and to show my support for Indian Country. I am proud to represent the #GrandRonde, #Siletz and #WarmSprings Tribes in Congress. pic.twitter.com/Mc7mGKfyuR

40 years ago the EPA began talking about banning asbestos, but it’s still being sold today. Asbestos kills 40,000 Americans every year. I voted for the #BanAsbestosNow Act in @EnergyCommerce. Asbestos exposure is a public health crisis. We can’t wait any longer to act! pic.twitter.com/7I4kA1UEBI
